=== ATTENTION: ===
Two images will be created by the "unpack.bat":

Sonic Adventure International (Repack) (English Speech) - DCRES.cdi
Sonic Adventure International (Repack) (Japanese Speech) - DCRES.cdi

Record the one with the speech you want, and select the proper option in the Options menu of the
game, else you won't hear any voice.
==================

Finally I was able to release a single disc release of Sonic Adventure with stereo sound. There
was a price  to pay though: japanese and english voices had to be separated in different discs and
videos quality suffered considerably. They are slighty better in the English voices disc (I had
extra ~5mb), but they got fine in both discs, and won't be a problem at all. I'm very proud of my
trade-off choices in this game, and I'm pretty sure you'll like it too. Dude, sound is stereo!

File order also has been more optimized.

Oh, and people who keep bothering about japanese voices: they're clearly not exactly the same of
english voices, so subtitles aren't the real translation. Blame the developers. So if you're not
sure what to use, I recommend the English version (even being the adapted japanese content, voices
and subtitles match), but it's your choice at the end.

Even being a NTSC-J region game, it will work in any region console as usual and it will have 5
languages for subtitles.

PAL users, the game will show 50/60hz selector when booting on your consoles.

Enjoy another nice DCRES work.


