--------------------------------------
Ripped: Internet feature; 2 not used music tracks (read more below).
Downsampled: Music and sound of videos monoized; videos downsampled (great quality, read more
below).
Source: GD dump.

This is the final version of Sonic Adventure for Dreamcast. I read that Sonic Adventure was
released under pressure to make it quick, so it came with a lot of glitches. This is a revised
version that correct them, and changed some other things. As far as I played, I noticed changes in
behaviour of first boss (Chaos 0), so there must be more changes in the game. Play it, find the
changes and tell me later :)

Note that although this is a japanese game, it has english voices and multi-language texts
included. It even has 50/60hz selector for PAL users. Primary language is selected according to
your bios configuration, but it can be changed in menu if you want.

This release has high quality media. Starting with the music. It was monoized using a high quality
decoder, so you hardly will notice any difference between this release and the original GD. I had
some problems working with loop tracks, but fortunately I had the same problem with Sonic Adventure
2 so I used the same program I made before and everything is working right now.

After that, I decided to keep the japanese voices, so I had very few space for videos. I deleted
web browser files, and ripped two tracks that are not played in the game (except in Sound Test).
They'reincluded in "Extras" folder in the pack, so check them if you want. I was almost finishing
thevideos when I got Sonic Adventure DX: Director's Cut for PC. I checked the files and found high
quality videos, so I decided using them as source, what would make quality of my videos much
higher. The only difference between this version videos and Dreamcast ones was logo in the
introduction video, then I edited it and merged the logo of Dreamcast video with the Sonic
Adventure DX, and it got perfect. You can't notice that the video was edited, even now that I told
you. Note that all resizing process were made with high quality filters, and videos were stored
using lossless codec. After having everything ready, I encoded them using VBR, what have a much
better quality/size ratio. The results? High quality videos. I could say they got better than the
original videos of Sonic Adventure, but instead, I will just challenge you to watch the videos and
say if you think they were downsampled or not.

Additionally, file order is the same of the original game (some optimizations were made later).

High quality music, better quality videos, better loadings... enjoy one more fantastic release by
DCRES!

Features of my release:
- Not corrupted files at all, it was made with GD dump files.
- Music monoized with high quality.
- Videos are better than in the original GD! Check them.
- Used GD file order, it means faster loadings and less Dreamcast reader noise.
- Selfboot.

About the game:
- It has VGA Box support.

Other comments:
- "Extras" folder in the pack contains some extra (duh!) stuff, including the two tracks that were
ripped and converted to MP3 and wallpapers included in the CD part of GD.
- Release comes with manual (of american version).